Create Table One using bllflow Object

Source: R/table-one-long.R
CreateTableOne.BLLFlow.Rd

Creates table one using the information present in the passed bllflow object specifically uses working data as the data, additional arguments can be passed to create a specific table one. However if no optional args are passed the variable info stored in variables MSW is used.

# S3 method for BLLFlow
CreateTableOne(
  x,
  vars = NULL,
  strata = NULL,
  factor_vars = NULL,
  select_role = NULL,
  ...
)

Arguments

x

The bllflow object
vars

The optional vars to use in creation of tableone if no vars are passed then vars in MSW variables is used
strata

The optional strata to use in creation of tableone if no strata is passed no strata is used
factor_vars

The optional factor_vars (categorical variables) used in creation of tableone if nothing is passed the MSW variables sheet is used to determine variable types
select_role

The optional argument that specifies the role of the variables to pass to tableone
...

Additional arguments to pass to the tableone::CreateTableOne function call

Value

returns a table one tableone object
